TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {20000=SUMMER 2012 Played for the Far West League Neptune Beach Pearl. AS A REDSHIRT SOPHOMORE | 2012 Hit .100 (1-for-10) with two RBI and two runs scored in 12 games played ... Made his first career start in right field against San Francisco ... In just his third at-bat of the season, recorded the first hit of his career - a home run - during Oregon’s 4-0 victory over Connecticut. AS A REDSHIRT FRESHMAN | 2011 Appeared in two games … Walked in his first at-bat in a 10-0 victory over BYU … Also appeared as a defensive replacement in the outfield against Portland. SUMMER 2010 Played for the Waimea Waves of the Hawaii Collegiate Baseball League … Batted .284 with 11 runs scored, nine RBI, six doubles and two triples. 2010 Redshirted. HIGH SCHOOL A 2009 graduate of Justin-Siena High School in Napa, Calif.… A two-sport athlete for the Braves playing both baseball and football … On the diamond was a catcher and infielder for head coach Scott Wright … Was a two-time All-Marin County Athletic League first-team selection in 2008 and 2009 … Was the Napa County Offensive Player of the Year in both 2008 and 2009 … On the football field was a linebacker and running back for head coach Rich Cotruvo … Had two touchdowns in the 2008 North Coast Section championship game … Was also a two-time first-team All-MCAL selection in 2007 and 2008. PERSONAL Born in Sonoma, Calif.… Parents are Mario and Theresa Pardini … Has one sister, Jenna … Majoring in economics.}
